About Us community manufactured and mobile homes
Bayonet Point Village
Bayonet Point Village Co-op is a friendly and well managed and maintained mobile home community that is located about 35 miles North of Tampa in New Port Richey, Florida. Perfect for active snowbirds and permanent residents alike.
Office hours are Monday through Friday from
9am-1pm
Eastern Time.
Bayonet Point Village Co-op is a 55+ Deed Restricted, Florida mobile home community. The park opened in 1985 and became resident owned, when it was purchased by the residents in 2004. Small pets are permitted and there is a limited amount of secured storage space available that residents can keep their cargo trailers and RV’s when not in use.
There are 163 home sites. All but 6 lots are occupied. These lots are available for placement of new homes. There are 82 residents who own shares and 74 residents who lease their lot. For shareholders, the monthly maintenance fee is $192.5. For those who lease, the monthly maintenance fees range from $438 to $513 per month, with most paying on the lower end. These fees include use of the clubhouse, a heated swimming pool, shuffleboard courts, lawn mowing and edging, trash removal and sewer, high speed internet and TV.
There is a pool table in the clubhouse. The community has paved streets and sidewalks, with ample lighting.
All homes are double-wide units which have a covered carport, cement driveway and an in-ground sprinkler system.
There is a listing of homes currently for sale. Homes are available with or without a share.
There are currently no shares available for sale.
It is important to note that all potential residents are required to pass a background and credit check, and are also required to have an interview with the Board of Directors.
Best kept secret in Florida. Friendly, active community, resident-owned and self-governed park located in a beautiful area about 30 minutes north of Tampa airport and about 6 miles east of the Gulf of Mexico. Robert K Rees Memorial Park has a beautiful beach and is about 12 miles away.
Our premier park of 156 homes provides a relaxed setting to bask in the Florida sunshine or watch a sunset. One of the best places on the west coast to watch a sunset is Robert J Strickland Memorial Park, about 7 miles away. We are a blend of permanent and seasonal residents from all over the United States and Canada sharing a common mission and vision for our community. Visit soon and allow us to show you how we can offer you affordable living in the beautiful state of Florida.  We look forward to seeing you! If we could answer any questions for you, please contact us.
